User Manual¶

The description for three Graphs¶

  • The first graph is electrical single line diagram for the Nordic 32 Test System.
  • The second graph show rate or range of the voltage change.
  • The third graph represents the page rank value computed by the edge weight equals to reactive power.

The User input and System Output¶

User input: Disconnect any of the edge.
System Output: It provides the animation to illustrate the complete procedure capture the power system intuition from the disturbance taken to the end – system self-recovery or blackout.

Some Statements¶

One: The user input text box is still under construction. In this demo, the main proposal is testing the output layout.
Two: For the two Graphs, The output procedure is illustrated by the changing color of the node.

Color Voltage flutuation Condition
Green < 10% Normal case
Blue 10% ~ 20% Abnormal
Red > 20% Abnormal

Table one - Color classification for graph two, the voltage collapse Graph.

Color Value
Blue Positive
Yellow Negative
In additional The greater the absolute value, the deeper the shade

Table two - Color classification for graph three, the reactive power weighted page rank Graph

The initial Graph or the Graph with no disturbance intake¶

Some example cases with a transmission Line disconnection:¶

There are three cases of result.

Case One:¶

The disturbance does not influence the power and voltage. Think if we disconnect a light in Lab, it will make no difference for the whole power system.

Case two:¶

The disturbance leads to relatively voltage flutuation and sufficient of reactive power. However, it does not cause the blackout.

Case three:¶

The disturbance cause a voltage casading and finally it lead to a blackout.
